You'll be happier if you install virtual env.
https://virtualenv.pypa.io/en/latest/installation.html

We are using Django 1.7.9 and Python 2.7.6.

python --version

Install Homebrew.  Follow the instructions at brew.sh.

sudo easy_install pip

sudo pip install virtualenv

sudo pip install Django==1.7.9

Install the Python Image Tools:
sudo pip install Pillow

Install Python Graphing Tools:
sudo pip install matplotlib

First you'll want a fresh database:
rm -f database/mysite.db
python manage.py syncdb

It's going to prompt you for a superuser.
admin/123456

Start the server with this:
python manage.py runserver

Here's how you get to the admin console:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/

Connect to the server with your browser:
http://127.0.0.1:8000/tracker/

Initialize the db with some data:
cp fixtures/me.png media/photos/
python manage.py loaddata fixtures/basic.json

